    "body": "Distinguish between \"not found\"-type errors, which are sometimes unimportant and which we may want to ignore, and \"other\" errors which usually do want to be propagated.\r\n\r\nThe main difference in behaviour is that `BaseException` (e.g. `MemoryError` etc) will now be propagated out of `__Pyx_MergeVtables`. It also means that if a base class has an attribute `__pyx_vtable__` which isn't a capsule that's now an error that is propagated rather than silently ignored.",
    "closed_at": null,
