                    "name": "da-woods"
                },
                "message": "Improve error handling in GetVtable\n\nDistinguish between \"not found\"-type errors, which are sometimes\nunimportant and which we may want to ignore, and \"other\" errors\nwhich usually do want to be propagated.\n\nThe main difference in behaviour is that `BaseException` (e.g.\n`MemoryError` etc) will now be propagated out of `__Pyx_MergeVtables`.\nIt also means that if a base class has an attribute `__pyx_vtable__`\nwhich isn't a capsule that's now an error that is propagated\nrather than silently ignored.",
